h1. create-unit-test-controller-spock

h2. Purpose

The @create-unit-test-controller-spock@ generates all the unit tests for a controller with the "Spock Framework":https://code.google.com/p/spock/

h2. Examples

{code:java}
grails create-unit-test-controller-spock Person
grails create-unit-test-controller-spock "*"
{code}

h2. Description

Given at least one domain class, this command creates unit tests for a controller with the "Spock Framework":https://code.google.com/p/spock/ . The command will generate the following files:
* @test/unit/{package}/{domainClass}ControllerIndexSpec.groovy@
* @test/unit/{package}/{domainClass}ControllerContentSpec.groovy@
* @test/unit/{package}/{domainClass}ControllerListSpec.groovy@
* @test/unit/{package}/{domainClass}ControllerCreateSpec.groovy@
* @test/unit/{package}/{domainClass}ControllerSaveSpec.groovy@
* @test/unit/{package}/{domainClass}ControllerEditSpec.groovy@
* @test/unit/{package}/{domainClass}ControllerUpdateSpec.groovy@
* @test/unit/{package}/{domainClass}ControllerDeleteSpec.groovy@

Usage:

{code:java}
grails create-unit-test-controller-spock [domainClass]
{code}

Arguments:
* @domainClass@ - Either a domain class name (case-sensitive) without its package or a wildcard (*). If you specify the wildcard the artifacts will be generated for all domain classes.
